Among the few dissatisfied from the right-wing ranks are the Bush era lamb, former U.N. ambassador John Bolton, who described the speech as “singular, bloody and uninspired,” as stated on the website National Review Online.
To the left of the president, for example, Democratic Representative Dennis Kucinich is frightened when he looks at Barack Obama justifying the use of force.
“When we wrap the war in the envelope of justice, we can easily justify the massacre of innocent people,” he warned.
