Illusory thoughts and hallucinations are based on reality, and the alienation of experience occurs within the real framework.
Scientists are still wondering why our brains are doing such things.
Exceptional states can lead to a short-term loss of touch with reality in any person, Fuchs says.
Not everyone develops into psychosis.
