Hallucinations are a typical accompanying phenomenon of psychosis, but also a surprising number of other diseases.
In addition to psychological disorders such as border personality or depression, they also often cause diseases such as migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis or Alzheimer’s disease or brain trauma.
Surprisingly, the brain of a healthy person itself hallucines under certain conditions.
