Schmidt-Degenhard examined the so-called oneiroid form of experience, a particular form of altered consciousness to dream.
Oneiroid states are highly complex, detailed fictional dreams that the person concerned considers real and can not even distinguish them backwards from the alert state.
Oneiroid state of consciousness occurs in extreme situations caused by trauma or illness, such as patients with polyradicular inflammation who experience motor paralysis at full consciousness.
